bio:
Born in Oregon, raised in San Francisco. Worked on audio and instrumentation projects at Ampex Corporation while earning engineering degree from Stanford. Played integral role in developing Ampex&#39s video tape recording system. After Ph.D. from Cambridge, became technical advisor for the United Nations in India. Returned to England in 1965 to found Dolby Laboratories. Opened California labs, manufacturing facilities in 1976. Licensed Dolby noise reduction technology became staple in audio equipment. Took Dolby Laboratories public in February; stake now worth $1.2 billion. Holds more than 50 patents. Enjoys skiing, boating and flying.
